Consider a relation scheme R = {A, B, C, D, E, H} on which the following functional dependencies hold:
{A -> B, BC -> D, E -> C, D -> A}
What are the candidate keys of R?

sourceQuestion:
The following functional dependencies are given:
AB -> CD, AF -> D, DE -> F, C -> G, F -> E, G -> A

Which one of the following options is FALSE?
A. {CF} -> {AEG}
B. {DG} -> {ABCEF}
C. {AF} -> {EG}
D. {AB} -> {DGF}

Consider the relation scheme R = {E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, M, N} and the set of functional dependencies
{ {E,F} -> {G},  {F} -> {I,J},  {E,H} -> {K,L},  {K} -> {M},  {L} -> {N} }
on R. What is the key for R?
A. {E,F}
B. {E,F,H}
C. {E,F,H,I}
D. {E}

